\Title {Distributed Memory Bus for Multi-Agent Campus Systems: Context Compression, Coordination Quality, and Policy-Aware Sharing}
\Author {Syed Abdullah\ Hassan}
\Copyright {Copyright \textcopyright \ 2026\ Syed Abdullah\ Hassan.\ Except otherwise noted, the reuse of this document is authorized under a Creative Commons 4.0 International (CC-BY-4.0) license.}
\CopyrightURL {https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/deed.en}
\Subject {This thesis designs, implements, and evaluates a distributed memory bus with a context-compression layer for multi-agent institutional systems. It contributes (i) a multi-agent coordination benchmark, (ii) an empirical characterisation of how context compression affects multi-agent coordination quality at 7B parameters with a 13B sanity arm, (iii) a catalogue of three retrieval-augmented generation pipeline architectures combining retrieval and compression under matched evaluation conditions, and (iv) a tag-preserving compressor variant integrated with a reference memory-bus implementation. The compute envelope is a single Apple M4 Pro 48 GB workstation, and the deliverable is the manuscript together with an open-source reference implementation.}
\Keywords [en] {multi-agent systems\sep large language models\sep context compression\sep retrieval-augmented generation\sep agentic memory\sep privacy-aware retrieval\sep [fi] monitoimijaj\"arjestelm\"at\sep suuret kielimallit\sep kontekstin tiivist\"aminen\sep hakuparannettu generointi\sep agenttinen muisti\sep yksityisyystietoinen haku}
